# Bilingual reply pattern (EN / 中文)

- For **every** assistant reply in this workspace, use **strict alternation**: one complete sentence in English, then one complete sentence in Chinese, then English, then Chinese, and so on.
- Cover the same meaning in each pair; keep sentences clear and natural in both languages.
- Code blocks, file paths, commands, and citations stay as usual; wrap explanatory prose around them in the alternating pattern when explaining.
- Do **not** merge two languages into one sentence unless quoting an identifier.
